Helicopters were deployed to water bomb a blaze in the town's Groenvlei community. CAPE TOWN - Firefighters in Knysna have attended to several flare-ups today. Officials say teams from the local fire station have been deployed to hotspot areas. Helicopters were deployed to water bomb a blaze in the town's Groenvlei community.Over ten thousand people had to be evacuated as runaway fires advanced towards their properties last week.The local municipality has rolled out assessment and infrastructure rebuilding programmes following the inferno.Fire Chief Clinton Manuel says the situation is under control. We will be monitoring the situation and deal with flare-ups as we go along. 